definitions: distance traveled or measured eastward, especially at sea

examples.text: with the help of the following breeze, she ran 650 miles of her easting down

definitions: a figure or line representing eastward distance on a map (expressed by convention as the first part of a grid reference, before northing)

examples.text: the Japanese sent a message that accidentally left out an easting and a northing in the plain text

shortDefinitions: figure or line representing eastward distance on map
